KWAITO star Mshoza might be seen as a gold digger by some, but she has a soft spot for those in need.Mshoza, real name Nomasonto Maswanganyi, has turned out to be a Good Samaritan for a university dropout.A third-year TV and Radio Broadcasting student, who dropped out of the University of Lesotho, turned to Mshoza for help.Retselisitsoe &ldquo;Tseli&rdquo; Seeqela read one of Mshoza&rsquo;s articles online and took Mshoza&rsquo;s number.&ldquo;I started texting her and told her she inspired me. She responded and she was so sweet.&ldquo;I saw the article that said she was giving away five bursaries and two homes. I thought to myself &lsquo;let me try this&rsquo;.&ldquo;I told her I&rsquo;m only left with one module to graduate,&rdquo; said Tseli.Tseli moved to Gauteng around February to look for a job in TV production and broadcasting, but ended up working at a restaurant at Maboneng Precinct, in Joburg.&ldquo;I was then contacted by Mshoza&rsquo;s manager,&rdquo; added Tseli.Mshoza said she wants people to prioritise education. &ldquo;And when it comes to Tseli, I wouldn&rsquo;t let someone suffer because of one module. &ldquo;The plan is to take her in now the year is almost over and then next year she&rsquo;ll go back to school full-time to finish her course. Then we&rsquo;ll take it from there,&rdquo; she said.